<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8899] MergeStrategy code creates HttpClient(s) and HttoSolrClient(s) that it does not close</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8899</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description></description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12953403">SOLR-8899</key>
            <summary>MergeStrategy code creates HttpClient(s) and HttoSolrClient(s) that it does not close</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/open.png" description="The issue is open and ready for the assignee to start work on it.">Open</status>
                    <statusCategory id="2" key="new" colorName="blue-gray"/>
                                    <resolution id="-1">Unresolved</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="-1">Unassigned</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="markrmiller@gmail.com">Mark Miller</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Thu, 24 Mar 2016 21:37:34 +0000</created>
                <updated>Wed, 13 Apr 2016 23:21:19 +0000</updated>
                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15216138" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 15:01:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This causes issues as HttpClient can do things like start threads and needs to be closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15216776" author="joel.bernstein" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 20:24:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The IterativeMergeStrategy has a static HttpClient, which was designed to be cached and used for all calls. it&apos;s not shutdown at all even when Solr is shutdown. I&apos;ll change that so it&apos;s shutdown and recreated after each use. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15216783" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2016 20:29:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, practically these things don&apos;t tend to matter, but we really want to clean up for tests that run in the same JVM, and it lets us add automation to ensure new code cleans up without adding annotation exceptions. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4509&quot; title=&quot;Move to non deprecated HttpClient impl classes to remove stale connection check on every request and move connection lifecycle management towards the client.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4509&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4509&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; moves to an HttpClient impl that starts threads, and it was already a good idea to shutdown the connection pool. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15239355" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2016 14:46:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 79195a8e540e2013a538860151a16b49c538418c in lucene-solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from markrmiller&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=79195a8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=79195a8&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8899&quot; title=&quot;MergeStrategy code creates HttpClient(s) and HttoSolrClient(s) that it does not close&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-8899&quot;&gt;SOLR-8899&lt;/a&gt;: Ignore thread leaks for this test - due to the HttpClient leak, the idle connection evictor thread can sometimes leak.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15240223" author="jira-bot" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2016 23:21:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 79195a8e540e2013a538860151a16b49c538418c in lucene-solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/jira/&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8908&quot; title=&quot;Registering each ZkIndexSchemaReader as an OnReconnect listener introduces a memory leak&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-8908&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-8908&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; from markrmiller&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=79195a8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=lucene-solr.git;h=79195a8&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8899&quot; title=&quot;MergeStrategy code creates HttpClient(s) and HttoSolrClient(s) that it does not close&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-8899&quot;&gt;SOLR-8899&lt;/a&gt;: Ignore thread leaks for this test - due to the HttpClient leak, the idle connection evictor thread can sometimes leak.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
